messages.content: What is the purpose of BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes repository?
The purpose of BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes repository is to store custom nodes created by BilboX for ComfyUI.
What are the dependencies for installing BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes?
The only dependency mentioned for installing BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes is having a working installation of git.
What is BilboX's PromptGeek Photo Prompt node?

BilboX's PromptGeek Photo Prompt node is a node created from PromptGeek's 'Creating Photorealistic Images With AI: Using Stable Diffusion' book data. It provides a convenient way to compose photorealistic prompts into ComfyUI.
What are the two preview modes offered by BilboX's PromptGeek Photo Prompt node?
The two preview modes offered by BilboX's PromptGeek Photo Prompt node are Tooltip mode and Modal mode.
What is the Vignette effect node in BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes?

The Vignette effect node in BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes is a fix and improvement of EllangoK's ComfyUI-post-processing-nodes vignette effect. It has two parameters: one for the size of the effect and another for the opacity.
What is the LUT color correction node in BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes?

The LUT color correction node in BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes is an implementation of Yoonsikp's pycubelut as a post-processing effect in Comfy-UI. It allows applying LUT files to color correct images.
Who are the authors of BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes?
The authors of BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes are BilboX for the code and @PromptGeek Youtube for the arts.
What is the license for BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes?
BilboX's ComfyUI Custom Nodes project is licensed under the MIT License.
